  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\ni just found that some tx hashes are duplicated on Ethereum and Ethereum classic network. Few years ago, after a hardfork there was issue with replay attacks, but i think it was fixed in 2017. \r\n\r\nExample transaction hash -> 0x8577d2ce7e033ea14517296b9a0f9879265701741e990f15de6a56b42eadb708\r\n\r\n\r\nThis transaction has same addresses from -> to, same value, same timestamp, just asset is different.\r\nhttps://blockscout.com/etc/mainnet/tx/0x8577d2ce7e033ea14517296b9a0f9879265701741e990f15de6a56b42eadb708\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/tx/0x8577d2ce7e033ea14517296b9a0f9879265701741e990f15de6a56b42eadb708\r\n\r\nCould someone explain how is it possible? ",
