    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Reason being that this is a legacy transaction, where replay protection is implemented by incorporating the chain id into an existing field. For legacy transctions, doing so is not mandatory - as opposed to newer types where the chain id is it's own explicit field. \r\n\r\nSo someone intentionally made a replayable transaction and put on both networks. \r\n![Screenshot 2022-12-06 at 11-33-09 Ethereum Transaction Hash (Txhash) Details Etherscan](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/142290/205887844-070ead29-9fef-432f-91f0-f95e7859d5bf.png)\r\n",
